Place the black chickpeas in the slow cooker. In a food processor, puree the onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, and green chiles into a paste. Add this mixture to the slow cooker. Add the cumin, turmeric, red chile powder, salt, and water to the slow cooker. Cook on high for 9 hours. Using the back of a spoon, an immersion blender, or a regular blender, mash about a third of the beans. Add the cilantro and lemon juice. Serve with steaming bowls of basmati or brown rice.